          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-03-17 14:01:05" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the substance which bears the imprint of a seal or signet (see {L:σφραγίς&lt;SDBG:σφραγίς:000000&gt;}[a], {D:6.54}), used for sealing a document or for showing ownership or endorsement</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>seal</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:06600500200034} one may speak of ‘the wax that keeps the scroll closed,’ but in some languages it may be better to use a more general statement, for example, ‘the substance with which the scroll is sealed’ or ‘the substance that kept the scroll closed.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
